Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveThe date of the start of season seven of reality TV show, Big Brother Naija, has been announced.
In a post on its Instagram page on Tuesday, the organisers of the show, Multichoice, revealed that the launch weekend will be July 23 and 24th, 2022.
The Executive, Head of Content and West Africa channels, Multichoice Nigeria, Busola Tejumola, said, “The seventh edition will be different. I have been seeing a lot of tweets, speculations about what the season will be, what it will look like. I can confidently, tell you, you are all wrong. It will premiere with a double launch on the 23rd of July.”
